HEADWORD: Falsism
<hw>Fals"ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is
evidently false; an assertion or statement the falsity of which is
plainly apparent; -- opposed to <xex>truism</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Falsity</ent>⟦br⟧
